ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Have you ever gambled or bet too often or too much?
Did/do you frequently gamble larger amounts or over a longer period of time than you intend?
Did/do you need to increase the size or frequency of the bets to achieve excitement?
Did/do you become restless or irritable if you are unable to gamble?
Did/do you sustain repeated losses by trying to win back losses?
Were/are you frequently preoccupied with gambling?
Have you made repeated attempts to stop or reduce your gambling?
Have you frequently neglected family, social, or job obligations when you gamble?
Has gambling ever caused you to skip important social, job, or recreational activities?
Have you continued to gamble in spite of debts and/or other consequences?
Did/do you continue to gamble to escape from feelings such as sadness or depression, helplessness, guilt, anxiety?
Have you committed illegal acts such as forgery, fraud, theft, or embezzlement to finance gambling?
Did/do you rely on others to bail you out of financial crises caused by gambling?
Did/do you lie to family members, therapist or others to conceal the extent of your gambling?
INTERVIEWER: Count positive symptoms and enter here.
INTERVIEWER: Is the total Positive Sympotoms four or more?
How old were you when you first gambled heavily?
How old were you the last time you gambled heavily?
Have you ever sought help for a problem with gambling?
Did you have these problems other than during a mania?
